lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "findSecret")
  (signature ( (text str) ) str)
  (constraints
    (constraint "The input text contains a secret word at the very end.")
    (constraint "The secret word is separated by whitespace from other words in the text.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Read the provided text and find the secret word mentioned at the very end. Return only that word.")
    (rule "Split the input text into individual words using whitespace as a delimiter.")
    (return "The last word from the split list of words is the secret word to be returned.")
  )
)
generated_code:
# solution.py
from typing import List, Optional, Dict, Set, Any
import re

class Solution:
    def findSecret(self, text: str) -> str:
        """Read the provided text and find the secret word mentioned at the very end. Return only that word."""
        
        # Split the input text into individual words using whitespace as a delimiter.
        words = re.split('\s+', text)
        
        # The last word from the split list of words is the secret word to be returned.
        return words[-1] if len(words) > 0 else ""
